cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper discusses network virtualization and the design of algorithms for resource allocation and service migration. The primary focus is on improving quality of service (QoS) for thin client applications on mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses optimization problems and competitive analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper presents algorithms with provable performance guarantees, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
